Welcome to the Void Desktop Live system. 

The live desktop should launch at any moment.

In case it doesn't, two users are available to log in for troubleshooting:

	- root
	- anon

The `anon` user additionally has `sudo(8)` permissions to run any command
without a password.

To start the installation, open a terminal and run:

    `sudo void-installer`

and follow the on-screen instructions. To install additional software make
sure to configure your network interface and then use:

	- xbps-install(1) to install/update packages
	- xbps-query(1) to query for package info

The Void Linux Handbook is also available for offline access in multiple
formats, and can be accessed with the `void-docs(1)` utility.

Additionally, you may find extra documentation related to Void Desktop at:

`https://github.com/canofjuice/void-desktop-mklive/wiki`

Thanks for trying out Void Desktop and cheers to the Void Linux developers for making an awesome linux distribution!

    https://www.github.com/canofjuice/void-desktop-mklive
    https://www.voidlinux.org

